data-triple-N3.o: "Huddersfield Town Football Club is an English football club formed in 1908 and based in Huddersfield, West Yorkshire. Huddersfield Town have played the majority of their history in the top two tiers of English football and they currently play in The Championship. Their current manager is Mark Robins, who was appointed as manager on 14 February 2013. Their current chairman is local businessman Dean Hoyle, who took over from previous chairman Ken Davy on 3 June 2009."@en
